Package edu.wpi.grip.core.sockets

Interface Socket<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value that this socket stores
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    InputSocket<T>, OutputSocket<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CudaSocket, InputSocket.Decorator, InputSocketImpl, OutputSocketImpl, SocketImpl
    public interface Socket<T>
    A Socket is an abstract wrapper for a value that can be updated and passed around operations. Sockets contain a set of hints about the data they contain, as well as an actual value. Sockets that are given to operations are InputSockets, and sockets that operations store their results are OutputSockets.

      • onValueChanged

        default void onValueChanged()
        Called when the value for the socket is reassigned. Can be used by an implementing class to change behaviour when the value is changed.

      • flagChanged

        default void flagChanged()
        Notifies this socket that the value changed. This is usually only needed for sockets that contain mutable data such as images or other native classes (Point, Size, etc) that are written to by OpenCV operations.
